		<content type="html" xml:base="https://love2d.org/forums/viewtopic.php?p=211246#p211246"><![CDATA[
Yes there is. With the latest stable version (<a href="https://github.com/Yonaba/Jumper/tree/jumper-1.8.1-1" class="postlink">1.8.1</a>), you can turn off diagonal searching <br>But actually it will work fine with most of search algorithm, except Jump Point Search. I remember I had a lot of troubles to get it to work with JPS since the original algorithm were not defined in such a way it can handle orthogonal moves only. Finally I came up with something buggy for JPS, but which will be fixed in a next release of the library.<br>See the documentation about <a href="http://yonaba.github.io/Jumper/docs/modules/jumper.pathfinder.html#pathfinder:setMode" class="postlink">pathfinder:setMode()</a> for more details.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3394">Roland_Yonaba</a> — Thu Mar 30, 2017 3:46 pm</p><hr />
